s%20murder%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Minneapolis%20police%2C%20many%20white%20residents%20of%20Jasper%20sought%20to%20assuage%20their%20Black%20neighbors%20that%20they%20would%20come%20together%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20horrific%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnation%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fjames-byrd-murder-jasper-texas%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20Washington%20Post%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20describes%20a%20town%20that%20in%20many%20ways%20has%20sought%20to%20move%20forward%20while%20downplaying%20a%20crime%20that%20for%2025%20years%20has%20defined%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20reported%20that%20Byrd%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20local%20school%20district's%20textbooks%20on%20history%20in%20the%20Lone%20Star%20State.%20The%20crime%20perpetuated%20upon%20Byrd%20is%20also%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Jasper%20County%20Historical%20Museum%2C%20which%20has%20been%20open%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Byrd's%20family%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20local%20officials%20haven't%20offered%20much%20support%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20keep%20Byrd's%20name%20alive%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELouvon%20Byrd%20Harris%2C%20Byrd's%20younger%20sister%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20many%20people%20simply%20%26quot%3Bwant%20to%20forget%20what%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20know%20who%20people%20really%20are%20once%20the%20cameras%20are%20gone.%20And%20once%20the%20cameras%20were%20gone%2C%20people%20started%20saying%2C%20'Poor%20Jasper%2C%20we're%20victims%2C%20too%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Shultz%2C%20one%20of%20the%20two%20white%20members%20on%20the%20Jasper%20City%20Council%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20residents%20continue%20to%20bear%20the%20burden%20%E2%80%94%20unfairly%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20horrific%20crime.%20(Two%20of%20the%20men%20who%20killed%20Byrd%20have%20already%20been%20executed%20by%20the%20state%