te%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20much%20has%20changed%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20retired%20nursing%20aide%20Betty%20Lane%20told%20The%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EWhile%20Byrd's%20murder%20prompted%20the%20Texas%20legislature's%202001%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2001%2F05%2F12%2Fus%2Fgovernor-of-texas-signs-a-hate-crimes-bill.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20Hate%20Crimes%20Act%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcrt%2Fmatthew-shepard-and-james-byrd-jr-hate-crimes-prevention-act-2009-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealong%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Matthew%20Shepard%20and%20James%20Byrd%20Jr.%20Hate%20Crimes%20Prevention%20Act%2C%20which%20passed%20by%20Congress%20was%20signed%20into%20law%20in%202009%2C%20his%20family%20has%20still%20sought%20to%20do%20more%20to%20keep%20his%20legacy%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20murder%2C%20the%20family%20launched%20the%20Byrd%20Foundation%20for%20Racial%20Healing.%20And%20they%20sought%20to%20open%20a%20museum%20that%20would%20be%20focused%20on%20racial%20reconciliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EBut%20a%20lack%20of%20funding%20ended%20those%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20Jasper%20County%20Historical%20Museum%2C%20the%20institution's%20part-time%20director%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20they're%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20inform%20the%20public%20about%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20working%20on%20how%20to%20address%20it%20as%20a%20museum%2C%26quot%3B%20Tod%20Lawlis%20told%20The%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3ELawlis%2C%20who%20is%20white%2C%20said%20that%20he%20found%20out%20about%20a%20Byrd%20exhibit%20that%20was%20in%20Austin%2C%20the%20state%20capital%2C%20but%20was%20unsure%20if%20it%20would%20be%20showcased%20in%20Jasper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20make%20arrangements%20to%20see%20it%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20fair%2C%20we%20want%20to%20try%20to%20get%20it%20here.%20It%20is%20part%20of%20the%20county's%20history.%20We%20want%20to%20tell%20it%20in%20an%20unbiased%2C%20fair%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-byrd-jr-jasper-texas-dragging-murder-hate-crime-racism-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693080775000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ea50d2bc26b40019908952%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-byrd-jr-jasper-texas-dragging-murder-hate-crime-racism-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Washington%20Post%20report%20describes%20a%20town%20that%20in%20many%20ways%20has%20sought%20to%20move%20forward%20while%20downplaying%20a%20crime%20that%20for%20years%20has%20defined%20the%20area.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-byrd-jr-jasper-texas-dragging-murder-hate-crime-racism-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%2