lion%20was%20an%20anomaly%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20consequences%20were%20indeed%20inevitable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%3A%20The%20crash%20was%20no%20accident.%20It%20was%20unavoidable%20payback%20for%20Prigozhin's%20insubordination%2C%20which%20culminated%20in%20a%20march%20towards%20Moscow%20with%20a%20column%20of%20his%20Wagner%20Group%20mercenaries.%20The%20march%20was%20a%20stunningly%20open%20challenge%20to%20the%20authority%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20the%20man%20who%20had%20found%20Prigozhin%20when%20he%20was%20running%20a%20string%20of%20Saint%20Petersburg%20restaurants%20and%20made%20him%20into%20one%20of%20Russia's%20most%20feared%20power%20brokers%2C%20trafficking%20in%20weaponry%2C%20gold%2C%20and%20armed%20men%20across%20three%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Prigozhin%20himself%2C%20the%20former%20Kremlin%20official%20scoffed%20at%20the%20idea%20that%20his%20death%20was%20an%20untimely%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHis%20death%20could%20not%20have%20been%20more%20timely%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHis%20life%20was%20that%20of%20Chekov's%20gun.%20When%20his%20blank%20was%20fired%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20left%20to%20do%20but%20be%20swept%20behind%20the%20curtain%20and%20let%20the%20play%20carry%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20invoking%20Chekhov's%20gun%2C%20the%20official%20was%20suggesting%20that%20any%20private%20military%20force%20that%20refused%20to%20submit%20to%20Putin's%20direct%20control%20was%20destined%20to%20be%20crushed%20by%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20famous%20storytelling%20principle%20%E2%80%94%20a%20gun%20innocently%20hanging%20on%20the%20wall%20in%20a%20play's%20first%20act%20will%20be%20fired%20in%20its%20third%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20of%20Russian%20literature's%20great%20contributions%20to%20world%20culture.%20But%20the%20story%20of%20Prigozhin's%20rise%20and%20fall%20can%20also%20be%20told%20through%20a%20trove%20of%20internal%20files%20that%20exposed%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20his%20corporate%20empire%20in%20the%20months%20before%20his%20death.%20Those%20files%20included%20dozens%20of%20detailed%20spreadsheets%20showing%20how%20Prigozhin's%20Wagner%20Group%20tracked%20and%20spent%20its%20money%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWages%20for%20a%20Nigerian%20gig%20worker%20to%20push%20Kremlin%20memes%20through%20a%20troll%20farm%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%24276.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuel%20to%20light%20up%20a%20famous%20hillside%20sign%20in%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20%E2%80%94%20%24791.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorldwide%20promotion%20budget%20for%20%26quot%3BTourist%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20feature%20film%20depicting%20heroic%20Russian%20mercenaries%20who%20save%20an%20African%20government%20from%20local%20bandits%20and%20European%20elites%2C%20including%20ads%20on%20TikTok%2C%20YouTube%2C%20and%20Google%20%E2%80%94%2029%20million%20rubles%2C%20or%20roughly%20%24300%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20files%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyevgeny-prigozhin-wagnerleaks-wagner-putin-hack-mexico-trolls-facebook-instagram-2023-2%5C%22%3Eobtained%20from%20anonymous%20hackers%20who%20had%20pried%20them%20loose%20from%20the%20Wagner%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20show%20why%20Prigozhin%20was%20so%20useful%20to%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20not%20only%20in%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20in%20surreptitious%20campaigns%20to%20influence%20US%20politics%20and%20extend%20Russia's%20reach%20throughout%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa.%20Even%20before%20we%20reviewed%20evidence%20of%20Wagner%20troops%20engaging%20in%20rape%2C%20beheadings%2C%20and%20other%20war%20crimes%2C%20Prigozhin%20was%20known%20to%20be%20a%20bloodthirsty%20warlord%2C%20an%20ex-convict%20and%20Saint%20Petersburg%20restaurateur%20who%20had%20taken%20the%20brutal%20logic%20that%20he'd%20learned%20during%20his%20years%20in%20the%20Russian%20prison%20system%20to%20the%20global%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20spreadsheets%20showed%20us%20that%20Prigozhin%20was%20more%20than%20that.%20He%20was%20a%20bloodthirsty%20warlord%20who%20knew%20how%20to%20stretch%20a%20buck.%20The%20tiny%20amounts%20of%20money%20that%20we%20saw%20meticulously%20accounted%20for%20in%20the%20Wagner%20Group's%20monthly%20budgets%20and%20expense%20reports%20were%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20American%20or%20European%20would%20have%20spent%20on%20similar%20overseas%20operations.%20Of%20course%2C%20that%20money%20was%20supplemented%20by%20pillage%20and%20extortion.%20The%20files%20included%20a%20shakedown%20letter%20Prigozhin%20had%20sent%20to%20the%20Syrian%20government%2C%20demanding%20oil%20revenue%20from%20a%20tract%20of%20land%20that%20his%20men%20had%20taken%20back%20from%20ISIS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20uses%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20to%20boost%20its%20military%20strength%2C%20but%20it%20is%20nothing%20like%20a%20conventional%20fighting%20force%20or%20diplomatic%20corps.%20Though%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20private%20military%20company%20%E2%80%94%20mercenaries%20%E2%80%94%20Wagner's%20brutal%20methods%2C%20semi-official%20status%2C%20and%20appetite%20for%20resource%20extraction%20makes%20them%20something%20closer%20to%2016th-century%20privateers.%20For%20so%20long%20as%20he%20remained%20loyal%2C%20Prigozhin%20was%20a%20perfect%20instrument%20for%20Putin%20to%20build%20up%20Russia's%20superpower%20status%20despite%20having%20an%20economy%20less%20than%20a%20tenth%20the%20size%20of%20China%20or%20the%20US.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20two%20months%20between%20the%20time%20that%20Prigozhin%20marched%20on%20Moscow%20and%20the%20explosion%20onboard%20his%20private%20plane%2C%20it%20wasn't%20impossible%20to%20imagine%20that%20Prigozhin%20had%20made%20himself%20so%20indispensable%20to%20Putin%20that%20he%20might%20be%20forgiven.%20Putin%20had%20already%20shown%20a%20remarkable%20tolerance%20of%20Prigozhin's%20grandiosity%20and%20his%20propensity%20to%20take%20to%20social%20media%20and%20publicly%20castigate%20the%20Kremlin's%20favorite%20generals%20for%20bad%20strategy%20and%20supply%20problems%20in%20Ukraine.%20Prigozhin's%20death%20suggests%20that%20Putin%20has%20accepted%20a%20setback%20in%20Russia's%20global%20ambitions%20in%20favor%20of%20ensuring%20the%20stability%20of%20his%20own%20regime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20he'd%20prefer%20to%20have%20both.%20New%20reporting%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Frussia%2Fprigozhin-wagner-plane-crash-last-days-2c44dd5c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20how%20vigorously%20Putin%20was%20attempting%20to%20supplant%20Prigozhin's%20authority%20during%20the%20final%20weeks%20of%20his%20life%2C%20maintaining%20Wagner's%20African%20shadow%20empire%20while%20centralizing%20control%2C%20and%20how%20Prigozhin%20continued%20to%20antagonize%20the%20Kremlin%20by%20refusing%20to%20fade%20into%20the%20background.%20After%20the%20mutiny%2C%20Russian%20authorities%20punched%20back%2C%20raiding%20Wagner's%20offices%2C%20blocking%20their%20social%20media%20channels%2C%20and%20releasing%20photographs%20of%20Prigozhin's%20lavish%20apartment%20filled%20with%20cash%2C%20gold%2C%20and%20guns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20they%20did%20not%20do%20was%20file%20criminal%20charges%20against%20Prigozhin%20or%20his%20Wagner%20minions%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20they'd%20killed%20some%2015%20Russian%20service%20members%20during%20their%20aborted%20march%20to%20Moscow.%20This%20led%20some%20to%20believe%20that%20Putin%20and%20Prigozhin%20could%20come%20to%20terms%2C%20including%20Alexander%20Lukashenko%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Belarus%2C%20who%20fancied%20himself%20a%20peacemaker%20between%20the%20two%20men.%20But%20in%20fact%2C%20Putin%20appears%20to%20have%20busied%20himself%20with%20absorbing%20the%20Wagner%20empire%20into%20the%20Russian%20state%20while%20plotting%20his%20reven