%20as%20a%20just%20forum%20for%20trade%20and%20regulatory%20policy.%20The%20five%20BRICS%20nations%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-expansion-finalised-as-egypt-iran-ethiopia-argentina-saudi-and-uae-invited-to-join%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOut%2520of%2520the%2520six%2520countries%2Cgiven%2520%25E2%2580%2593%2520with%2520all%2520but%2520Ethiopia.%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20full%20admission%20of%20six%20new%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Argentina%2C%20Ethiopia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Egypt%20and%20the%20UAE.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbout%2050%20other%20heads%20of%20state%20and%20government%20attended%20the%20summit%2C%20underscoring%20the%20appeal%20of%20BRICS%2C%20which%20represents%20at%20its%20core%20the%20aspirations%20of%20developing%20countries%20for%20a%20greater%20role%20in%20the%20global%20financial%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20world%20is%20looking%20for%20answers%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.br%2Fplanalto%2Fpt-br%2Facompanhe-o-planalto%2Fnoticias%2F2023%2F08%2Fem-declaracao-conjunta-lideres-do-brics-anunciam-a-entrada-de-seis-novos-paises%2Fjhb-ii-declaration-24-august-2023.pdf%5C%22%3EXV%20BRICS%20Johannesburg%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%20certainly%20gives%20the%20impression%20of%20forward%20momentum%2C%20with%20concern%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Euse%20of%20unilateral%20coercive%20measures%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20expressed%20at%20the%20outset%2C%20calls%20for%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Egreater%20representation%20of%20emerging%20markets%20and%20developing%20countries%20(EMDCs)%2C%20in%20international%20organisations%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Especial%20and%20differential%20treatment%20for%20developing%20countries%20in%20the%20WTO%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20pointing%20out%20the%20rising%20interest%20rates%20which%20have%20worsened%20debt%20vulnerabilities%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20and%20a%20demand%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eaddress%20the%20international%20debt%20agenda%20properly%E2%80%9D%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0BRICS%20has%20shown%20unity%20of%20purpose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20over%20%244%20trillion%20in%20foreign%20currency%20reserves%20and%2021%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20cover%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20the%20global%20economy.%20However%2C%20the%20full%20potential%20of%20BRICS%20economies%20is%20far%20from%20reached.%20Members%20comprehend%20this%2C%20and%20so%20the%20Johannesburg%20declaration%20calls%20for%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Cunlocking%E2%80%9D%20intra-BRICS%20cooperation%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20it%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20unleash%20through%20dialogue%20on%20payment%20instruments%20between%20emerging%20markets%20and%20developing%20countries%20(EMDCs).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20New%20Development%20Bank%20(NMD%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20BRICS%20Bank)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20concrete%20success%20of%20the%20grouping%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20a%20well-designed%20governance%20system.%20If%20one%20compares%20the%20BRICS%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20cumulative%20disbursements%20of%20%2414.6%20billion%20by%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20to%20the%20%2460%20billion%20disbursed%20by%20World%20Bank%20in%202021%2C%20the%20NDB%E2%80%99s%20lending%20programmes%20are%20minuscule.%20Nevertheless%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20central%20banks%20of%20BRICS%20nations%20seem%20ready%20to%20let%20go%20of%20the%20conservatism%20that%20has%20held%20back%20the%20BRICS%E2%80%99s%20lending%20potential.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENDB%20started%20expanding%20its%20membership%20in%20September%202021%20with%20the%20admission%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20UAE%20and%20Uruguay%3B%20subsequently%2C%20Egypt%20was%20admitted%20as%20a%20new%20member.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20as%20the%20ninth%20member%20would%20strengthen%20BRICS%E2%80%99s%20funding%20options%2C%20representing%20another%20deep-pocketed%20shareholder%20as%20the%20NDB%20assesses%20its%20ability%20to%20mobilise%20funds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO-300x175.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21155630%2FNDB-HQ-LOGO-1024x596.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669001%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22699%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20Development%20Bank%2C%20sometimes%20called%20BRICS%20bank.%20Photo%3A%20By%20Bb3015%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENDB%20is%20at%20the%20cusp%20of%20emerging%20as%20an%20alternative%2C%20as%20the%20West%20continues%20to%20maintain%20its%20traditional%20lock%20over%20the%20World%20Bank.%20But%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20order%20to%20make%20a%20worthy%20difference%20in%20global%20affairs%2C%20the%20BRICS%20bank%20will%20have%20to%20become%20more%20transparent%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Famid-sanctions-against-russia-brics-can-lead-the-change-towards-national-currency-payments%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emove%20forward%20with%20transformative%20ideas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20NDB%20could%20look%20to%20supplement%20its%20activities%20by%20collaborating%20with%20Beijing-based%20Asian%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20Bank%20(AIIB).%20Launched%20almost%20simultaneously%20in%202014%2C%20the%20capital%20structure%2C%20governance%20and%20operations%20of%20both%20these%20new%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20(MDBs)%20have%20been%20effective%20in%20addressing%20infrastructure%20investment%20deficit%20in%20developing%20countries.%20At%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brics.utoronto.ca%2Fdocs%2F150709-ufa-declaration_en.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWe%2520welcome%2520the%2520proposal%2520for%2Cand%2520its%2520entry%2520into%2520force.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVII%20summit%20in%20Ufa%2C%20BRICS%20explicitly%20declared%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20welcome%20the%20proposal%20for%20the%20NDB%20to%20cooperate%20closely%20with%20existing%20and%20new%20financing%20mechanisms%20including%20the%20Asian%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20Bank.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETaking%20that%20forward%2C%20the%20NDB%20and%20the%20AIIB%20should%20actively%20engage%20in%20co-financing%20projects%20with%20development%20institutions%20as%20well%20as%20commercial%20banks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20World%20Bank%20has%20been%20slow%20in%20reorienting%20its%20mission%20in%20the%20age%20of%20climate%20change.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202022%20Bridgetown%20Initiative%20proposed%20reforms%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%20mission%20with%20calls%20on%20wealthy%20countries%20to%20provide%20%24100%20billion%20per%20year%20in%20foreign%20exchange%20guarantees%20to%20low-income%20countries%20for%20decarbonisation%20efforts.%20But%20with%20this%20transformational%20reform%20yet%20to%20come%20about%20at%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20the%20BRICS%20position%20that%20poverty%20eradication%20and%20climate%20change%20are%20not%20exclusive%20is%20more%20attractive%20for%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Fnews%2Ffeature%2F2021%2F10%2F31%2Fcop26-the-world-is-watching%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewarming%20could%20push%20an%20additional%20132%20million%20people%20into%20poverty%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cspan%3EBy%20one%20estimation%2C%20EMDCs%20except%20China%2C%20will%20require%20a%20total%20annual%20investment%20of%20%241%20trillion%20by%202025%20and%20%242.4%20trillion%20by%202030%2C%20as%20such%2C%20Green%20Finance%20(GFN)%20has%20become%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20the%20BRICS%20economies.%20Because%20these%20countries%20are%20also%20the%20largest%20CO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20emitters%2C%20aggressive%20GFN%20initiatives%20are%20required.%20NDB%20has%20made%20a%20start%20by%20utilising%20%E2%80%98green%20bonds%E2%80%99%20(fixed-income%20securities%20that%20are%20used%20to%20finance%20environmental%20projects)%20to%20ensure%20that%20environmental%20activities%20are%20supported%20sustainably.%20Given%20these%20shifts%2C%20new%20MDBs%20could%20increase%20the%20volume%20of%20their%20operations%20severalfold%2C%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20global%20multilateral%20climate%20finance%2C%20bringing%20the%20disbursement%20amounts%20closer%20to%20the%20volume%20of%20infrastructure%20financing%20provided%20by%20major%20traditional%20banks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20misgivings%20that%20BRICS%20is%20a%20disparate%20group.%20India%20has%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20Chinese%20approach%20to%20development%20finance%20is%20shaped%20by%20complex%20economic%20and%20political%20interests.%20But%20in%20order%20to%20remain%20relevant%20in%20the%20context%20of%20multilateral%20development%20finance%2C%20it%20must%20recognise%20that%20because%20China%20is%20playing%20a%20prominent%20role%20in%20both%20the%20NDB%20and%20the%20AIIB%2C%20synergy%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20global%20financial%20governance%20through%20the%20BRICS%20mechanism%20may%20be%20the%20best%20way%20forward.%20There%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20reinforcing%20dialogue%20toward%20this%20perspective%2C%20between%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Johannesburg%20summit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20its%20expanded%20membership%20and%20relevant%20portfolio%2C%20BRICS%20should%20consider%20setting%20up%20a%20permanent%20secretariat%20which%20it%20does%20not%20have%20at%20the%20moment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20for%20all%20its%20discord%2C%20has%20underlined%20the%20disaffection%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20with%20the%20West%2C%20unlining%20the%20support%20Russia%20enjoys%20from%20its%20BRICS%20partners%20at%20a%20time%20of%20global%20isolation.%20The%20Johannesburg%20declaration%20which%20ends%20with%20the%20statement%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBrazil%2C%20India%2C%20China%20and%20South%20Africa%20extend%20their%20full%20support%20to%20Russia%20for%20its%20BRICS%20Chairship%20in%202024%20and%20the%20holding%20of%20the%20XVI%20BRICS%20Summit%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Kazan%2C%20Russia%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20could%20not%20emphasise%20this%20support%20better.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fvaishali-basu-sharma%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVaishali%20Basu%20Sharma%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20an%20analyst%20on%20strategic%20and%20economic%20affairs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693046722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24001805%2FF4NKlFIWcAAT_Qt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-summit-internal-cohesion-forward-momentum%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20summit%20underscored%20the%20wide%20appeal%20of%20BRICS%2C%20which%20represents%20at%20its%20core%20the%20aspirations%20of%2