s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EVIDEO%20%7C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20CM%20MK%20Stalin%20enjoys%20a%20meal%20with%20school%20children%20in%20Nagapattinam%20district%20as%20he%20launched%20the%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20breakfast%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20was%20initially%20launched%20to%20provide%20breakfast%20to%20over%201%20lakh%20students%20in%20classes%201%20to%205%20across%201%2C545%20government%20schools%2C%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FAc7KBSI4uF%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FAc7KBSI4uF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20(%40PTI_News)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1694908221876531270%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%2025%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmiles%20all%20around%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20minister%20Ma%20Subramanian%20inaugurated%20the%20programme%20at%20the%20Chennai%20Primary%20School%20at%20Manthope%20in%20Saidapet.%20As%20many%20as%201%2C075%20students%20of%20the%20school%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20stated%20that%20each%20student%20will%20be%20served%20cereals%20like%20semolina%2C%20wheat%2C%20rice%2C%20millet%2C%20and%20pulses%2C%20and%20locally%20available%20vegetables%20from%20Monday%20to%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20will%20be%20provided%20150%20to%20200%20grams%20of%20cooked%20food%20and%2060%20grams%20of%20sambar%20with%20vegetables.%20This%20is%20apart%20from%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20to%20students%20till%20Class%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES%20Paul%20Raj%2C%20a%20fifth-grade%20student%20at%20Chennai%20Primary%20School%20in%20Saidapet%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20boy%20used%20to%20attend%20school%20on%20an%20empty%20stomach%2C%20since%20his%20mother%20has%20to%20leave%20for%20work%20early%20and%20family%20has%20limited%20resources.%20On%20Friday%2C%20his%20face%20lit%20up%20when%20the%20school%20bell%20rang%2C%20announcing%20the%20breakfast%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaj%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20he%20had%20a%20satisfying%20meal%20of%20khichdi%2C%20sambar%20and%20kesari.%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20I%20would%20be%20famished%20by%2011%20am%20and%20eagerly%20wait%20for%20the%20bell%20to%20ring%20to%20have%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20at%20the%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20child%20grinned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMore%20than%2070%25%20of%20the%20students%20do%20not%20have%20breakfast%20at%20home.%20We%20were%20happy%20that%20the%20students%20enjoyed%20the%20breakfast.%20No%20one%20wasted%20the%20food.%20The%20dull%2C%20inactive%20faces%20of%20the%20children%20lit%20up%20with%20happiness%2C%E2%80%9D%20V.%20Umaparvathy%20at%20the%20Saidapet%20school%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1.jpeg%20750w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26121044%2FSchoolchildren-being-served-as-part-of-the-CMs-Breakfast-Scheme-now-extended-to-29000-more-schools-at-a-Chennai-school.-Laasya-Shekhar-e1692968973580-750x375-1-300x150.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669962%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESchoolchildren%20being%20served%20breakfast.%20Photo%3A%20Laasya%20Shekhar%2FSouth%20First%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EImproved%20attendance%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20positive%20impact%20of%20this%20programme%20extends%20far%20beyond%20filling%20empty%20stomachs.%20A%20recent%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20State%20Planning%20Commission%20found%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20attendance%20among%20government%20schools%20implementing%20the%20breakfast%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20out%20of%20the%201%2C543%20schools%20where%20children%20have%20been%20receiving%20breakfast%20since%2015%20September%2C%202022%2C%201%2C319%20schools%20witnessed%20a%20remarkable%20rise%20in%20attendance%20during%20January%20and%20February%2C%20compared%20to%20June-July%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20base%20attendance%20data%20of%20the%20initial%201%2C543%20beneficiary%20schools%20was%20compared%20against%20that%20of%20neighbouring%20schools%20within%201-2%20km%20by%20considering%20the%20geographical%20coordinates%20of%20the%20schools%2C%20reported%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Ffree-breakfast-scheme-has-improved-attendance-in-schools-tamil-nadu-govt-study-1200572.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20considered%20only%20schools%20with%20enrolment%20of%2025%20and%20above%20and%20schools%20with%20consistent%20attendance%20reporting%20above%2075%25.%20This%20left%20the%20study%20with%2072%20beneficiary%20schools%20each%20mapped%20with%20at%20least%20two%20to%2015%20neighbouring%20schools%2C%20which%20took%20the%20total%20to%20414.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuick%20rewind%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Breakfast%20Scheme%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20many%20pioneering%20schemes%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20providing%20food%20to%20the%20school%20children%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20an%20initiative%20that%20improved%20the%20attendance%20and%20reduced%20malnutrition%20among%20socially%20struggling%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1920%3A%20The%20then%20Mayor%20of%20Chennai%20Corporation%2C%20Sir%20PT%20Thiyagarayar%2C%20passed%20a%20resolution%20to%20implement%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20in%20Corporation%20School%20at%20Thousand%20Lights%2C%20Chennai.%20The%20scheme%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20school%E2%80%99s%20student%20strength.%20The%20scheme%20was%20expanded%20to%20a%20few%20more%20schools%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1947%3A%20Due%20to%20financial%20constraints%2C%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20was%20abandoned%2C%20except%20in%20Harijan%20Welfare%20Department-run%20schools.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1957%3A%20Chief%20minister%20K%20Kamaraj%20resumed%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20scheme%20for%20primary%20school%20students.%20%E2%82%B910%20lakh%20was%20allotted%20for%20implementing%20this%20scheme%2C%20with%20a%20clause%20that%20it%20should%20not%20exceeding%20%E2%82%B918%20per%20child%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1982%3A%20Chief%20minister%20MG%20Ramachandran%20introduced%20the%20Nutritious%20Meal%20Programme.%20Children%20in%20pre-school%20and%20primary%20schools%20were%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1989%3A%C2%A0%20Chief%20minister%20M%20Karunanidhi%20included%20an%20egg%20every%20two%20weeks%20to%20the%20menu%20of%20the%20nutritious%20meal%20scheme.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E1998-2008%3A%20The%20egg%20count%20gradually%20increased%20from%20one%20per%20week%20to%20three%20per%20week.%20The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20provided%20bananas%20for%20the%20children%20who%20would%20not%20eat%20eggs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E2010%3A%20Egg%20count%20goes%20to%20five%20every%20week.%3C%2Fli