%20extraordinariness%20of%20a%20gender%20curriculum%20lies%20in%20questioning%20hegemonic%20masculinity%20too.%20Patriarchy%20adversely%20impacts%20not%20only%20women%20but%20also%20men.%20Marginalised%20men%20are%20often%20subject%20to%20oppressive%20power%20operated%20by%20other%20men.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20classroom%20has%20to%20probe%20anxieties%20of%20%E2%80%98proving%E2%80%99%20one%E2%80%99s%20masculinity%20to%20blend%20solidarity%20between%20different%20genders.%20Interrogating%20ideas%20of%20heteronormative%20binaries%20could%20be%20a%20good%20beginning%20to%20naturalise%20sexually%20diverse%20identities.%20The%20association%20of%20aggression%20with%20masculine%20standards%20of%20success%2C%20power%20and%20vitality%20could%20be%20a%20moot%20point%20in%20understanding%20the%20dynamics%20of%20violence%20that%20plagues%20women%E2%80%99s%20lives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECognitive%20and%20moral%20development%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20curriculum%20has%20to%20do%20away%20with%20sexist%20standards%20of%20reason.%20Traditional%20learning%20tends%20to%20focus%20on%20curriculum%20as%20an%20object%20or%20textbook%20instead%20of%20an%20embodied%20world%20of%20children.%20New%20pedagogical%20techniques%20have%20to%20re-centre%20around%20feeling%2C%20empathy%20and%20passion.%20%E2%80%98Caring%E2%80%99%20in%20classrooms%20can%20propel%20more%20responses%20to%20conversations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20point%20is%20to%20create%20meaningful%20spaces%20for%20finding%20voices%20through%20coalescent%20argumentation%20that%20exposes%20gender%20stereotypes%20and%20intervenes%20in%20the%20institutional%20structures%20that%20sustain%20intersectional%20oppression.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20good%20example%20of%20such%20cognitive%20capacity%20building%20is%20through%20art%20education.%20Meanings%20to%20specific%20visual%20artworks%20can%20be%20discussed%20to%20allow%20students%20to%20think%20about%20how%20gender%20biases%20are%20inscribed%20to%20a%20work%20of%20art%20or%20even%20how%20students%20process%20an%20artwork%20from%20their%20gendered%20positionalities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20way%20forward%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20gender%20curriculum%20has%20to%20evolve%20for%20systemic%20change%20that%20infuses%20agency%20in%20teachers%20and%20students%20alike.%20By%20rendering%20visible%20gendered%20cultural%20inscriptions%2C%20it%20can%20benefit%20from%20dialogic%2C%20dialectically%20educative%20encounters%20in%20the%20classrooms.%20The%20transition%20from%20%E2%80%98the%20will%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20to%20%E2%80%98the%20will%20to%20become%E2%80%99%20must%20be%20a%20classroom%20habit.%20Agreeing%20with%20Judith%20Butler%2C%20the%20one-goal%20mission%20is%20%E2%80%98to%20think%20through%20the%20possibility%20of%20subverting%20and%20displacing%E2%80%99%20perversions%20of%20gendered%20ideas%20that%20interrupt%20the%20progress%20of%20any%20citizen.%20Transformative%20change%20in%20the%20attitudes%20of%20children%20will%20be%20the%20first%20step%20to%20revolutionise%20society.%20Delhi%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20shy%20away%20from%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnita%20Tagore%20is%20associate%20professor%20at%20Kalindi%20College%2C%20University%20of%20Delhi.%20She%20is%20a%20lawyer%20and%20socio-legal%20researcher.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693029653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F26110550%2FIMG_2635.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fgendering-the-education-revolution-in-delhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20unrecognised%20influence%20of%20gender%20in%20knowledge%20production%20needs%20nuanced%20classroom%20discussions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fgendering-the-edu